<title>USA: Penn Treaty names president.</title>
<headline>Penn Treaty names president.</headline>
<dateline>ALLENTOWN, Pa. 1997-04-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Penn Treaty American Corp said Friday it named Glen Levit president, from vice president of sales and regional sales director of the company's insurance subsidiaries.</p>
<p>The company said it also named A.J. Carden as executive vice president and chief operating officers of the insurance subisidiaries.</p>
<p>Levit, an Allentown, Pa., resident, is also a director of Penn Treaty and its units.</p>
<p>Carden, who also lives in Allentown, has been a director and has served as executive vice president of the company and its units, overseeing the companies' claims, underwriting and compliance departments, since 1983.</p>
<p>The company did not say whom they replaced.</p>
